cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with image processing and machine learning techniques for iris recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of different filters and kernels, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper presents a framework for data-driven kernel learning, which could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
